29. tum enim gerebat. i. e. a man who had been elected to a magistracy by vote of the people had to get his electiori ratified before he actually entered upon his duties. This right of the patrician senators to revise the decrees of the comitia centuriata was limited in 339 13.c. by the Lem Publilia, which compelled the senate to give this sanction before the measure was voted on (Livy 8. 12. 15 ante initum snffrayium).
